OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA band of wet and rather windy
OL,6,Fweather will feed eastwards across the
OL,7,Fcountry this morning. Much sunnier
OL,8,Fskies will follow during the
OL,9,Fafternoon, perhaps with isolated
OL,10,Fshowers developing later, and the
OL,11,Fbrisk winds will ease a little too.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA few showers are possible in
OL,14,Fthe north and west overnight,
OL,15,Fotherwise dry with clear spells.
OL,16,FLighter winds, allowing a few fog
OL,17,Fpatches to form, and staying frost-
OL,18,Ffree.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
